sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Isolated human islets were treated with an adenovirus to overexpress a constitutively active (ca) Nfatc2 protein or GFP. Islets were collected for ATAC-seq 48 hours later.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: 48 hours after GFP or Nfatc2 adenoviral transduction, 50 average sized human islets were picked into a 1.7 mL tube. The islets were washed with 500 uL of PBS at 4C and pelleted by centrifugation at 100 x g for 1 minute. 300 uL of ATAC Lysis buffer (10 mM Tris-HCl pH 7.4, 10 mM NaCl, 3 mM MgCl2, 0.1% IGEPAL CA-630) was used to resuspend the islets. The islets were incubated for 20 minutes on ice. After incubating, the islets were lysed by trituration with a 25 gauge needle essentially until intac ...
sample_data_processing: Illumina Nextera adapters were trimmed with cutadapt (version 2.0) with option “-q 30 --minimum-length 36”., Paired-end ATAC-seq reads were aligned to the human genome assembly (hg19) with bowtie2 (version 2.3.4.1) with option “-X 800 --no-mixed --no-discordant”., For each sample, unmapped reads were filtered out by using SAMtools view (version 1.8), with option “-F 4” and mitochondrial reads were removed., Duplicate reads were removed with Picard tools (version 2.9.2), In total, 231,232 master  ...

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Isolated human islets were treated with an adenovirus to overexpress a constitutively active HA-tagged Nfatc2 protein. Islets were collected for ChIP-seq 48 hours later.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: ~17,000 human IEQs were incubated with 5 mL of 1% formaldehyde (Thermo Scientific, Cat. # 28906) in PBS for 5 minutes at room temperature. To quench the formaldehyde fixative, 256 uL of 2.5 mM glycine was added, incubated for 2 minutes, and then centrifuged (500 x g) to pellet the islets. Islets were washed with 1mL each of PBS, NCP buffer 1 (10 mM HEPES pH 6.5, 10 mM EDTA, 0.5 mM EGTA, 0.25% Triton X-100) and NCP buffer 2 (200 mM NaCl, 10 mM HEPES pH 6.5, 1 mM EDTA, 0.5 mM EGTA). Islets were th ...
sample_data_processing: The raw reads from all samples were aligned to human reference genome (hg19) with Bowtie 2 (version 2.3.1)., We used Bowtie2 default reporting mode with the argument -X 550 --no-mixed --no-discordant being specified., Picard MarkDuplicates tool (version 2.9.2) was used to remove duplicate reads from the alignment., We performed peak calling from mapped and properly paired reads with Bioconductor package MOSAiCS (version 3.5)., The peak sets called from the six samples were merged and 8,635 peaks ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: bigWig files contain the Nfatc2 peaks identified from 6 human islet samples.bigBed file contains the merged peaks used to determine Nfatc2 binding in human islets.

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Isolated human islets were treated with an adenovirus to overexpress a constitutively active HA-tagged Nfatc2 protein. Islets were collected for ncRNA-seq 48 hours later.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: The human islets were lysed with 350 uL of QIAzol Lysis Reagent (Qiagen) and stored at -80˚C before purifying RNA using Mini RNeasy purification kits per manufacturer’s instructions. Total RNA was treated with RiboZero purification and oligo-dT depletion in order to enrich for ncRNAs., RNA Barcoded Libraries were prepared according to Illumina's instructions (2013) accompanying the TruSeq RNA Sample prep kit v2 (Part# RS‐122‐2001).
sample_data_processing: Non-coding RNAseq data analysis was performed as described in Perez-Cervantes and Smith et al. 2020., Briefly, Fastq files were aligned to UCSC genome build hg19 using STAR (v2.5.1)., Transcript assembly was performed by Stringtie (version 1.3.3) and merged with the Stringtie ‘merge’ function., Counts were retrieved from the merged transcriptome with HTseq (v0.6), False discovery rate (FDR) was calculated after removing the coding-gene transcripts, ncRNA that overlapped coding genes in the same  ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: bigWig files of ncRNA enriched read abundance.csv file of ncRNA abundance.

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Isolated human islets were treated with an adenovirus to overexpress a constitutively active HA-tagged Nfatc2 protein. Islets were collected for ncRNA-seq 48 hours later.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: The human islets were lysed with 350 uL of QIAzol Lysis Reagent (Qiagen) and stored at -80˚C before purifying RNA using Mini RNeasy purification kits per manufacturer’s instructions. Total RNA was treated with RiboZero purification and oligo-dT depletion in order to enrich for ncRNAs., RNA Barcoded Libraries were prepared according to Illumina's instructions (2013) accompanying the TruSeq RNA Sample prep kit v2 (Part# RS‐122‐2001).

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Isolated human islets were treated with an adenovirus to overexpress a constitutively active (ca) Nfatc2, ca-Nfatc1 or GFP. Islets were collected for RNA-seq 48 hours later.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: The human islets were lysed with 350 uL of QIAzol Lysis Reagent (Qiagen) and stored at -80˚C before purifying RNA using Mini RNeasy purification kits per manufacturer’s instructions., Total RNA submitted to the University of Wisconsin-Madison Biotechnology Center was verified for purity and integrity via the NanoDrop2000 Spectrophotometer and Agilent 2100 BioAnalyzer, respectively. Samples that met the Illumina sample input guidelines were prepared according the TruSeq® Stranded Total RNA Sample ...
sample_data_processing: The human islet RNA-sequencing reads were mapped via bowtie against the refseq hg19 reference., Gene expression values were then estimated via RSEM., Expected transcripts per million were normalized using median-by-ratio normalization.
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited text file of transcripts per million (TPM)

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: The human islets were lysed with 350 uL of QIAzol Lysis Reagent (Qiagen) and stored at -80˚C before purifying RNA using Mini RNeasy purification kits per manufacturer’s instructions., Total RNA submitted to the University of Wisconsin-Madison Biotechnology Center was verified for purity and integrity via the NanoDrop2000 Spectrophotometer and Agilent 2100 BioAnalyzer, respectively. Samples that met the Illumina sample input guidelines were prepared according the TruSeq® Stranded Total RNA Sample ...
sample_data_processing: The human islet RNA-sequencing reads were mapped via bowtie against the refseq hg19 reference., Gene expression values were then estimated via RSEM., Expected transcripts per million were normalized using median-by-ratio normalization.
